                        Pr. 15.17 Betteris a dinner of green herbs

where loue is, then a ſtalled oxe, and hatred therewith. Yea, Better is a dry morſell,Pr. 17.1. if peace be with it; then an houſe full of ſacrifices with ſtrife. And if he find ſometime cauſe of blame;Pr. 19.11. The diſcretion of a man differreth his anger, and his glory is to paſſe by an offence:Pr. 17.9. 
