                        Forraine Congregations.
                        
                           
                              17. O the faireſt among women, whether is thy Welbeloued gon? whither is thy Welbeloued turned aſide, that we might ſeeke him with theeSInce thy Welbeloued is ſo glorious, and amiable (O thou which art for thy beauty worthie to bee the Spouſe of ſuch an husband) tell vs (for thou onely knoweſt it; and to ſeek Chriſt without the church we knowe is vain) tel vs where this Sauiour of thine is to bee ſought; that we (rauiſhed alſo with the report of his beautie) may ioin with thee in the ſame holy ſtudie of ſeeking after him.
                     
                  
                  
                     
                     CHAP. VI.
                     
                        MY Welbeloued Sauiour (if you vvould knowe this alſo) is to bee ſought and found in the particular aſſemblies of his people,
                              1. My welbeloued is gone down in to his garden to the beds of ſpices, to feed in the gardens and to gather lillies. which are his garden of pleaſure, wherin are varieties of all the beds of renued ſoules, which both he hath planted, and dreſſed by his continuall care, and wherin hee walketh for his delight; feeding and ſolacing himſelfe vvith thoſe fruites of righteouſneſſe, and new obedience, which they are able to bring forth vnto him.
                        And now loe,
                              2. I am 
                                 •
