                        The Church.
                        
                           
                              14. Oh my welbeloued, flee away, and be like vnto the Roe, or to the yong Hart vpon the mountaines of ſpices.I Will moſt gladly doe what thou commaundeſt, O my Sauiour but, that I may performe it accordingly; be thou

(which art, according to thy bodily preſence, in the hyeſt heauens) euer preſent with me by thy ſpirit, &amp; haſten thy glorious comming, to my full redemption.
                     
                  
